How do I make some text bounce up and down forever? How do I make a button cycle through a list of actions when pressed? These are the questions I found answers to recently. Both of them deal with cyclical processes but were achieved (in my case) in two different fashions.

Lets start with the second scenario first. I have a button, and when pressed the first time, I want it to move a div to the right. When pressed the second time, I want it to move the div down. Third to the left, and fourth up. Since, after I press the button the fourth time the div is back to it's starting location, I want the button to repeat the previous steps over and over and over again.

The key to this puzzle is a simple statement of:

if (n == 5) { n = 1 }

